# Component Docs Generator

Build the S2A in-Figma tech spec kit using `.sheet frame` surfaces, `.step` bullets, live component instances, and S2A design tokens throughout.

## Doc sheet sections (in order)
1. **Anatomy** — labeled callout canvas with black 20px badge circles, blue leader lines
2. **Properties** — table of all component properties with type, default, description
3. **Layout & Spacing** — token-annotated spacing diagram
4. **Accessibility** — WCAG 2.2 AA criteria with SC codes and plain-language summaries
5. **Usage** — do/don't examples with real component instances

## Surface tokens
- Sheet background: `s2a/color/background/subtle` (`VariableID:6:47`)
- Cards/rows: `s2a/color/background/default` (`VariableID:6:49`)
- Dividers: `s2a/color/border/subtle` (`VariableID:6:22`)

## Voice and tone
Write like an educator explaining to someone new. Say what something does and why it matters before the technical detail. No Figma API jargon (`INSTANCE_SWAP`, `primaryAxisSizingMode`). Keep token names and CSS property names exact.

## Anatomy callout style
- Black 20px badge circles (not blue)
- No stroke on cards — fills only
- State labels as text above cards ("Default state")
- Legend as vertical list: badge + stacked title/description
- Blue leader lines at 0.7 opacity, 1.5px weight
